Hmm, I think a tuple in Scala is even more expensive than a `TopicPartition` instance, and we are using one more map for that...

I think by just using the following pattern:

```
Set<TopicPartition> partitions = records.partitions();

for (partition <- partitions) {
Iterable iter = records.records(partition).iter()
}
```

Anyways, allocating a new object is in the order of ns, so if it is actually more awkward we can keep the old pattern.
